{"id":"astro-ph/9811369","submitter":"Marina Romanova","authors":"R.V.E. Lovelace, M.M. Romanova, G.S. Bisnovatyi-Kogan","title":"Magnetic propeller outflows","comments":"5 pages, 2 figures, emulapj.sty Replace: new Figure 2","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1086/306945","report-no":null,"categories":"astro-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  A model is developed for magnetic `propeller'-driven outflows which cause a\nrapidly rotating magnetized star accreting from a disk to spin-down. Energy and\nangular momentum lost by the star goes into expelling most of the accreting\ndisk matter. The theory gives an expression for the effective Alfven radius\n$R_A$ (where the inflowing matter is effectively stopped) which depends on the\nmass accretion rate, the star's mass and magnetic moment, and the star's\nrotation rate. The model points to a mechanism for `jumps' between spin-down\nand spin-up evolution and for the reverse transition, which are changes between\ntwo possible equilibrium configurations of the system. In for example the\ntransistion from spin-down to spin-up states the Alfven radius $R_A$ decreases\nfrom a value larger than the corotation radius to one which is smaller. In this\ntransistion the `propeller' goes from being ``on'' to being ``off.'' The ratio\nof the spin-down to spin-up torque (or the ratio for the reverse change) in a\njump is shown to be of order unity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Nov 1998 18:37:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 27 Nov 1998 19:54:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
